<topic id="d1e59"><title>Exercise 3.4</title><body><p>
<b>Express the component of
<d4p_eqn_inline>
    <mathml><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>v</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="true">⟶</m:mo></m:mover></m:math></mathml>
  </d4p_eqn_inline> perpendicular to
<d4p_eqn_inline>
    <mathml><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>w</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="true">⟶</m:mo></m:mover></m:math></mathml>
  </d4p_eqn_inline> in terms of dot products.</b>
</p><p>
Solution:
</p><p>
The component of 
<d4p_eqn_inline>
  <mathml><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>v</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="true">⟶</m:mo></m:mover></m:math></mathml>
</d4p_eqn_inline>
 perpendicular to 
<d4p_eqn_inline>
  <mathml><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>w</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="true">⟶</m:mo></m:mover></m:math></mathml>
</d4p_eqn_inline>
 is the magnitude of the projection of 
<d4p_eqn_inline>
  <mathml><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>v</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="true">⟶</m:mo></m:mover></m:math></mathml>
</d4p_eqn_inline>
 perpendicular to 
<d4p_eqn_inline>
  <mathml><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>w</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="true">⟶</m:mo></m:mover></m:math></mathml>
</d4p_eqn_inline>
. By
<ph outputclass="a">definition</ph>
this projection is 
<d4p_eqn_inline>
  <mathml><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>v</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="true">⟶</m:mo></m:mover></m:math></mathml>
</d4p_eqn_inline>
 minus the projection of 
<d4p_eqn_inline>
  <mathml><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>v</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="true">⟶</m:mo></m:mover></m:math></mathml>
</d4p_eqn_inline>
 in the direction of 
<d4p_eqn_inline>
  <mathml><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>w</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="true">⟶</m:mo></m:mover></m:math></mathml>
</d4p_eqn_inline>
.
<br/>
But the projection of 
<d4p_eqn_inline>
  <mathml><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>v</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="true">⟶</m:mo></m:mover></m:math></mathml>
</d4p_eqn_inline>
 in the direction of 
<d4p_eqn_inline>
  <mathml><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>w</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="true">⟶</m:mo></m:mover></m:math></mathml>
</d4p_eqn_inline>
 is 
<d4p_eqn_inline>
  <mathml><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:mfrac><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>v</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="true">⟶</m:mo></m:mover><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>w</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="true">⟶</m:mo></m:mover><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>w</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="true">⟶</m:mo></m:mover><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>w</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="true">⟶</m:mo></m:mover><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mfrac><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>w</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="true">⟶</m:mo></m:mover></m:mrow></m:math></mathml>
</d4p_eqn_inline>
.
<br/>
The projection of 
<d4p_eqn_inline>
  <mathml><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>v</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="true">⟶</m:mo></m:mover></m:math></mathml>
</d4p_eqn_inline>
 normal to 
<d4p_eqn_inline>
  <mathml><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>w</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="true">⟶</m:mo></m:mover></m:math></mathml>
</d4p_eqn_inline>
 is then 
<d4p_eqn_inline>
  <mathml><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>v</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="true">⟶</m:mo></m:mover><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>v</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="true">⟶</m:mo></m:mover><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>w</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="true">⟶</m:mo></m:mover><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>w</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="true">⟶</m:mo></m:mover><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>w</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="true">⟶</m:mo></m:mover><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mfrac><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>w</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="true">⟶</m:mo></m:mover></m:mrow></m:math></mathml>
</d4p_eqn_inline>
, the component of 
<d4p_eqn_inline>
  <mathml><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>v</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="true">⟶</m:mo></m:mover></m:math></mathml>
</d4p_eqn_inline>
 normal to 
<d4p_eqn_inline>
  <mathml><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>w</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="true">⟶</m:mo></m:mover></m:math></mathml>
</d4p_eqn_inline>
 is then the square root of the dot product of this projection with itself, or 
<d4p_eqn_inline>
  <mathml><m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:msup><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>v</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="true">⟶</m:mo></m:mover><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>v</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="true">⟶</m:mo></m:mover><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>v</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="true">⟶</m:mo></m:mover><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>w</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="true">⟶</m:mo></m:mover><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo><m:mo>*</m:mo><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>w</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="true">⟶</m:mo></m:mover><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>v</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="true">⟶</m:mo></m:mover><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>w</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="true">⟶</m:mo></m:mover><m:mo>,</m:mo><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>w</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="true">⟶</m:mo></m:mover><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mfrac></m:mrow><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mo>/</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup></m:mrow></m:math></mathml>
</d4p_eqn_inline>
.
</p></body></topic>